name: places/ChIJtSWVqA8Q2jER4pDxDNMNoLI/reviews/ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnTUNJdXR1MkRnEAE
text: {'text': '★★★☆☆\n\nMiam Miam offers a wide variety of French-Japanese fusion dishes, but unfortunately, none truly stand out in terms of flavor. The menu is extensive, covering everything from pasta to soufflés, which is great for those who like options. However, the execution feels a bit average—nothing particularly memorable or worth coming back for. Service was decent, and the ambiance is cozy enough for a casual meal. It’s not a bad place, but if you’re looking for something exceptional, this might not be it.', 'languageCode': 'en'}

name: places/ChIJtSWVqA8Q2jER4pDxDNMNoLI/reviews/ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VPbk9pcGZXM2RiYkR3EAE
text: {'text': 'Nice ambience, cosy and spacious. Service very good, the staff were smiling and prompt even when we dined at a peak period with all tables taken. A lot of food choices, for adults and kids. Portion was decent, I had space for dessert after that as well.', 'languageCode': 'en'}

name: places/ChIJtSWVqA8Q2jER4pDxDNMNoLI/reviews/ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnTURvdnJ2d2pRRRAB
